WEBVTT

1
00:02:32.653 --> 00:02:35.057
Darling Drusilla...

2
00:03:41.352 --> 00:03:43.631
I have existed from
the morning of the world

3
00:03:43.711 --> 00:03:47.839
and I shall exist until the last star
falls from the heavens.

4
00:03:47.919 --> 00:03:51.012
Although I have taken
the form of Gaius Caligula,

5
00:03:51.092 --> 00:03:53.940
I am all men
as I am no man and so...

6
00:03:54.441 --> 00:03:55.721
I am a god.

7
00:05:44.435 --> 00:05:47.967
- What's it like with Marcellus?
- What's what like?

8
00:05:49.435 --> 00:05:51.173
He's so fat!

9
00:05:51.815 --> 00:05:53.290
He's disgusting.

10
00:05:53.370 --> 00:05:54.304
He's not.

11
00:05:54.435 --> 00:05:56.320
He's only large.

12
00:05:56.895 --> 00:05:58.986
But tiny where it counts.

13
00:06:00.465 --> 00:06:01.957
How do you know?

14
00:06:03.659 --> 00:06:05.537
I saw him at the baths.

15
00:06:09.580 --> 00:06:11.898
Poor... poor Drusilla.

16
00:06:12.947 --> 00:06:14.398
You are vile.

17
00:06:19.331 --> 00:06:21.104
- Hold!
- Messenger for the prince!

18
00:06:21.184 --> 00:06:22.802
- Identify yourself!
- Macro.

19
00:06:25.781 --> 00:06:27.446
- Password?
- Justice.

20
00:06:48.492 --> 00:06:49.148
Prince?

21
00:06:53.252 --> 00:06:54.385
Forgive me, prince.

22
00:06:55.977 --> 00:06:58.107
The Emperor commands you
to wait upon him.

23
00:06:58.919 --> 00:07:00.290
What does he want?

24
00:07:00.370 --> 00:07:01.773
A last look at you perhaps.

25
00:07:02.406 --> 00:07:03.357
He is 77.

26
00:07:04.152 --> 00:07:05.190
May he live forever.

27
00:07:11.213 --> 00:07:13.000
How is Ennia?

28
00:07:13.080 --> 00:07:17.273
My wife lives only for the day
she can see you again, prince.

29
00:07:20.896 --> 00:07:21.940
Wait outside.

30
00:07:40.005 --> 00:07:41.679
What does all this mean?

31
00:07:42.747 --> 00:07:44.352
Take care, Little Boots.

32
00:07:45.684 --> 00:07:49.517
- Pray to Isis for me.
- I'll follow you as soon as I can.

33
00:08:04.255 --> 00:08:06.114
I hate coming back here, Macro.

34
00:08:09.117 --> 00:08:10.575
He's planning something.

35
00:08:12.372 --> 00:08:16.708
You've nothing to fear.
I command the Praetorian guards.

36
00:08:16.788 --> 00:08:18.773
With Tiberius, there's
always something to fear.

37
00:08:19.953 --> 00:08:21.770
Be very careful of Nerva.

38
00:08:21.850 --> 00:08:23.903
They say he can even tell
what you're thinking.

39
00:08:28.926 --> 00:08:29.602
Nerva!

40
00:08:29.682 --> 00:08:31.411
- Prince!
- Dear friend!

41
00:08:32.101 --> 00:08:35.464
Ten years is a long time
for the Emperor to be hidden away.

42
00:08:35.544 --> 00:08:39.843
I should feel a great deal happier
if he was back in Rome where he belongs.

43
00:08:39.923 --> 00:08:41.885
Tell me, how is the Emperor?

44
00:08:42.788 --> 00:08:44.760
Old, like me.

45
00:08:44.840 --> 00:08:46.523
I mean, how is his mood?

46
00:08:47.995 --> 00:08:49.760
Like the weather.

47
00:08:49.840 --> 00:08:51.732
But the weather's good today.

48
00:08:52.419 --> 00:08:53.357
Changeable.

49
00:08:57.810 --> 00:08:59.817
I've heard that during the last month,

50
00:08:59.897 --> 00:09:02.967
seven of my colleagues in the senate
have been put to death.

51
00:09:03.047 --> 00:09:04.118
For treason.

52
00:09:04.933 --> 00:09:07.023
Nine to be exact.

53
00:09:07.143 --> 00:09:11.065
Five of them cheated.
They killed themselves.

54
00:09:12.018 --> 00:09:13.959
That wasn't playing fair.

55
00:09:15.274 --> 00:09:16.898
Don't you agree, Nerva?

56
00:09:18.826 --> 00:09:20.315
They were all good men.

57
00:09:23.958 --> 00:09:27.273
If they were all good men, how could
their beloved Emperor find them guilty?

58
00:09:28.483 --> 00:09:30.482
You have a gift for logic, prince.

59
00:10:21.673 --> 00:10:22.898
Caligula!

60
00:10:30.734 --> 00:10:33.464
- Beloved grandfather.
- Do your dance, boy.

61
00:10:35.054 --> 00:10:37.065
- My dance?
- Yes.

62
00:10:37.145 --> 00:10:39.982
The one that you delighted the army with
when your father made you its mascot.

63
00:10:40.827 --> 00:10:41.482
Come on...

64
00:10:42.054 --> 00:10:43.315
Little Boots.

65
00:10:46.878 --> 00:10:48.190
I've forgotten it, lord.

66
00:10:48.612 --> 00:10:50.033
Oh, dance for me.

67
00:10:51.079 --> 00:10:52.255
Delight me.

68
00:10:53.893 --> 00:10:54.747
Dance!

69
00:11:06.354 --> 00:11:07.982
My little fishies.

70
00:11:08.595 --> 00:11:09.653
Fishies.

71
00:11:12.517 --> 00:11:14.911
Alright, my little fishies!

72
00:11:14.991 --> 00:11:15.755
Come in!

73
00:11:16.237 --> 00:11:17.607
All of you!

74
00:12:15.648 --> 00:12:16.607
Stop that!

75
00:12:40.864 --> 00:12:42.529
Out, little fishies!

76
00:12:43.049 --> 00:12:45.215
You've had enough for today!

77
00:12:49.352 --> 00:12:51.043
- Caligula!
- Yes, my lord?

78
00:12:51.123 --> 00:12:54.188
Why do you say such monstrous
things about me at Rome?

79
00:12:54.268 --> 00:12:58.440
- I hear you often pray for my death.
- I don't, lord, ever.

80
00:12:58.560 --> 00:12:59.815
You do not?

81
00:13:00.579 --> 00:13:03.438
By heavens, Caesar, I swear I do not.

82
00:13:03.518 --> 00:13:05.876
You do not in...

83
00:13:05.960 --> 00:13:06.773
in public.

84
00:13:09.393 --> 00:13:10.357
Never, lord.

85
00:13:11.039 --> 00:13:12.343
Remember this.

86
00:13:13.263 --> 00:13:15.398
That I have let you lived...

87
00:13:19.041 --> 00:13:20.249
so far.

88
00:13:21.898 --> 00:13:23.648
My little fishies love me.

89
00:13:25.001 --> 00:13:26.982
Innocents, you see.

90
00:13:30.541 --> 00:13:32.751
I protect their innocence.

91
00:13:33.515 --> 00:13:35.452
It is the least I can do...

92
00:13:36.041 --> 00:13:37.876
for it is a foul world.

93
00:13:37.956 --> 00:13:39.043
Away now!

94
00:13:42.535 --> 00:13:44.982
Nerva is scowling at us.

95
00:13:45.102 --> 00:13:46.244
Help me, Nerva.

96
00:13:47.001 --> 00:13:50.273
Help me transform this young barbarian
into a Roman Caesar.

97
00:13:50.393 --> 00:13:55.440
There have been three Roman Caesars:
Julius, Augustus and yourself.

98
00:13:56.302 --> 00:13:58.565
- Which do you want him to be?
- Best.

99
00:13:59.100 --> 00:14:01.315
That would be your father, Augustus.

100
00:14:01.435 --> 00:14:04.982
You see, Caligula,
I'm insulted to my face.

101
00:14:07.424 --> 00:14:08.815
Nerva, dear friend,

102
00:14:09.341 --> 00:14:11.440
watch out for Macro when I'm dead.

103
00:14:13.393 --> 00:14:14.679
I know.

104
00:14:15.292 --> 00:14:18.385
- He hates me...
- Because you are wise.

105
00:14:19.768 --> 00:14:21.771
Because you are good.

106
00:14:22.529 --> 00:14:24.535
So when I'm gone,

107
00:14:25.440 --> 00:14:26.690
watch out for Macro.

108
00:14:29.346 --> 00:14:31.648
I've taken my precautions, Caesar.

109
00:14:34.624 --> 00:14:36.607
What might they be?

110
00:14:41.918 --> 00:14:43.732
Heaven help Rome!

111
00:14:44.976 --> 00:14:46.232
For I'm gone.

112
00:14:48.128 --> 00:14:49.394
I am old.

113
00:14:50.152 --> 00:14:52.273
Yes, lord, but you will live forever.

114
00:14:52.353 --> 00:14:57.898
All my family are dead but you,
child Gemellus and that...

115
00:14:58.018 --> 00:14:59.565
Claudius, that uncle.

116
00:15:01.086 --> 00:15:03.446
The others struck down by fate.

117
00:15:06.103 --> 00:15:09.773
And it is fate, Little Boots,
that rules us,

118
00:15:09.893 --> 00:15:11.195
not any god.

119
00:15:11.659 --> 00:15:13.107
You are a god, lord.

120
00:15:15.673 --> 00:15:16.773
No, I'm not!

121
00:15:17.281 --> 00:15:18.835
Not even when I'm dead.

122
00:15:18.918 --> 00:15:21.268
Julius Caesar and Augustus Caesar,

123
00:15:21.348 --> 00:15:22.482
they are gods.

124
00:15:22.956 --> 00:15:26.755
So say the Senate and so
the people prefer to believe.

125
00:15:26.835 --> 00:15:28.122
Such myth they use.

126
00:15:37.909 --> 00:15:39.480
Little Boots,

127
00:15:39.560 --> 00:15:42.273
- just look at you.
- Yes, Caesar?

128
00:15:48.835 --> 00:15:49.940
I am mercy.

129
00:15:50.402 --> 00:15:51.898
A viper...

130
00:15:52.293 --> 00:15:53.835
in Rome's bosom.

131
00:16:08.221 --> 00:16:09.065
Uncle!

132
00:16:24.263 --> 00:16:25.398
Caligula!

133
00:16:26.352 --> 00:16:29.190
Do you think this boy have been drinking?

134
00:16:30.826 --> 00:16:33.793
- I think he has, Caesar.
- So do I. Macro.

135
00:16:33.873 --> 00:16:36.148
- Yes, lord?
- Bring him more wine.

136
00:16:36.268 --> 00:16:37.636
And waste none.

137
00:16:45.635 --> 00:16:47.394
Remove your bootlaces.

138
00:17:28.793 --> 00:17:31.562
And what do they say of me at Rome?

139
00:17:31.642 --> 00:17:34.505
Oh, well, they need you, lord,
and they miss you.

140
00:17:35.011 --> 00:17:38.499
Most of my life I have given
to the Roman people.

141
00:17:38.631 --> 00:17:40.565
I have fought.

142
00:17:41.800 --> 00:17:43.065
I have given all.

143
00:17:46.818 --> 00:17:48.972
Aren't they lovely?

144
00:17:49.052 --> 00:17:50.232
Yes, lord.

145
00:17:50.352 --> 00:17:51.751
The satyrs are from Illyria.

146
00:17:54.055 --> 00:17:54.773
And... uh...

147
00:17:57.854 --> 00:17:58.887
This nymph...

148
00:18:00.208 --> 00:18:01.898
is from...
Where are you from?

149
00:18:03.852 --> 00:18:04.887
Britain, lord.

150
00:18:06.008 --> 00:18:06.834
Britain.

151
00:18:07.732 --> 00:18:10.398
- Speaking statues.
- Yes, yes.

152
00:18:10.478 --> 00:18:12.648
And they do more than speak.

153
00:18:13.299 --> 00:18:14.607
They do...

154
00:18:17.598 --> 00:18:19.190
You prefer nymphs to satyrs?

155
00:18:20.357 --> 00:18:22.148
I like both, lord.

156
00:18:22.228 --> 00:18:26.230
One needs both, yes.
To keep healthy.

157
00:18:29.477 --> 00:18:31.183
Rome is a republic

158
00:18:31.263 --> 00:18:34.273
and you and I are playing citizens.

159
00:18:34.623 --> 00:18:36.398
More confection!

160
00:19:02.102 --> 00:19:02.990
That's it.

161
00:19:27.750 --> 00:19:30.023
That's the best of my stallions.

162
00:19:31.685 --> 00:19:33.534
Serve the state, Caligula,

163
00:19:34.185 --> 00:19:36.898
although the people in it
are wicked beasts.

164
00:19:37.387 --> 00:19:39.682
- But they love you, lord.
- Oh, no!

165
00:19:40.290 --> 00:19:41.273
No.

166
00:19:41.353 --> 00:19:42.687
They fear me.

167
00:19:44.340 --> 00:19:45.903
And that is much better.

168
00:19:52.185 --> 00:19:53.898
I have no choice, you see.

169
00:19:54.426 --> 00:19:55.565
No choice.

170
00:19:56.936 --> 00:19:57.482
No choice?

171
00:19:59.071 --> 00:20:01.626
All I wanted was private life.

172
00:20:02.864 --> 00:20:05.815
I did not truly want
to become Emperor,

173
00:20:05.935 --> 00:20:06.916
but I had to.

174
00:20:06.996 --> 00:20:07.732
Had to?

175
00:20:07.852 --> 00:20:11.690
If someone else had become Emperor,
I would have been killed.

176
00:20:13.910 --> 00:20:14.773
As you will be.

177
00:20:18.996 --> 00:20:20.029
Will be?

178
00:20:26.800 --> 00:20:28.446
Will be gra... gr...

179
00:20:51.928 --> 00:20:53.815
Will be, grandfather?

180
00:20:54.176 --> 00:20:56.824
Would be, if you were not my heir.

181
00:20:58.060 --> 00:21:01.899
When Rome was just a city
and we were just citizens,

182
00:21:01.979 --> 00:21:03.934
known to one another.

183
00:21:04.014 --> 00:21:05.009
Do you see?

184
00:21:05.674 --> 00:21:10.607
My, we were frugal, good,
disciplined and dignified.

185
00:21:18.355 --> 00:21:20.953
The Romans I rule
are not what they were.

186
00:21:21.722 --> 00:21:22.906
They lust...

187
00:21:23.507 --> 00:21:26.690
they lust for power and pleasure.

188
00:21:27.001 --> 00:21:30.122
Money... the wives of other men...

189
00:21:31.098 --> 00:21:34.418
Oh, yes, I am a true moralist.

190
00:21:35.310 --> 00:21:37.543
And stern as any Cato.

191
00:21:40.310 --> 00:21:42.621
Fate chose me to govern swine.

192
00:21:42.701 --> 00:21:45.852
In my old age
I am become a swine-herd.

193
00:21:47.646 --> 00:21:50.987
You faithless boy
has drunk enough wine.

194
00:21:51.067 --> 00:21:52.857
I think he's drunk enough, lord.

195
00:21:52.977 --> 00:21:54.107
So do I.

196
00:22:09.852 --> 00:22:12.418
Now he is happy.

197
00:22:13.811 --> 00:22:16.010
Homer! You would not know that?

198
00:22:16.090 --> 00:22:18.421
You were educated in army camps only.

199
00:22:18.501 --> 00:22:20.482
You will know enough to be a swine-herd.

200
00:22:20.562 --> 00:22:23.732
Caesar, the Senate sends
these documents for your signature.

201
00:22:23.852 --> 00:22:24.786
Of course.

202
00:22:32.185 --> 00:22:34.828
The revised list of candidates
for the Equestrian Order.

203
00:22:34.908 --> 00:22:38.331
I, Tiberius Caesar, command in the name
of the Senate and the people...

204
00:22:39.001 --> 00:22:40.065
of Rome.

205
00:22:41.755 --> 00:22:44.483
Tax assessment, for Asia Minor,
Brescia and Gaul.

206
00:22:44.563 --> 00:22:48.927
I, Tiberius Caesar, command in the name
of the Senate and the people of Rome.

207
00:22:55.850 --> 00:22:57.065
Senator guilty of treason.

208
00:22:57.834 --> 00:23:00.765
Every senator believes himself
to be a potential Caesar,

209
00:23:00.845 --> 00:23:03.995
therefore every senator
is guilty of treason.

210
00:23:04.685 --> 00:23:06.552
In thought, if not in deed.

211
00:23:07.185 --> 00:23:11.398
The Senate is the natural enemy
of any Caesar, Little Boots.

212
00:23:11.518 --> 00:23:12.740
Remember that.

213
00:23:12.820 --> 00:23:14.148
Traitors. Look at them.

214
00:23:17.560 --> 00:23:18.419
Traitors.

215
00:23:20.798 --> 00:23:25.773
They offered to prove any law I made
before I made it.

216
00:23:25.893 --> 00:23:28.949
I said: "What if I go mad?
What then?"

217
00:23:31.317 --> 00:23:32.440
No answer.

218
00:23:33.314 --> 00:23:36.660
They were born to be slaves,
Germanicus, never forget that.

219
00:23:36.790 --> 00:23:40.090
I'm not Germanicus, lord.
I'm his son, Caligula.

220
00:23:40.190 --> 00:23:42.690
Yes. And your friend is Macro.

221
00:23:44.114 --> 00:23:48.315
- He serves you and only you, lord.
- And his wife is your friend, too.

222
00:23:48.435 --> 00:23:50.233
Is she friendly in bed?

223
00:23:51.115 --> 00:23:53.295
We must ask Macro that, lord.

224
00:23:53.375 --> 00:23:54.982
She seems friendly.

225
00:23:55.463 --> 00:23:57.482
And your sister, Drusilla...

226
00:23:58.608 --> 00:24:01.374
My sister is my sister, lord.

227
00:24:02.501 --> 00:24:05.815
I know everything
that is said and done.

228
00:24:07.128 --> 00:24:08.898
And thought.

229
00:24:10.821 --> 00:24:14.982
The setting sun
and the rising moon.

230
00:24:18.768 --> 00:24:19.690
Gemellus!

231
00:24:20.207 --> 00:24:21.773
Lovely boy.

232
00:24:21.893 --> 00:24:24.429
And too young to betray me.

233
00:24:24.509 --> 00:24:26.232
Well, perhaps not too young.

234
00:24:27.653 --> 00:24:30.672
Yes. Kiss your old grandfather.

235
00:24:30.752 --> 00:24:32.623
Yes, my last grandson.

236
00:24:33.322 --> 00:24:35.860
I am your grandson, too, Caesar.

237
00:24:35.940 --> 00:24:37.171
By adoption.

238
00:24:38.157 --> 00:24:41.148
This is the last flesh of my flesh.

239
00:24:42.221 --> 00:24:45.112
Poor boy.
What's to become of you?

240
00:24:45.192 --> 00:24:47.040
He's like a brother to me, lord.

241
00:24:47.120 --> 00:24:50.177
Brother? You know what a brother
is in our family?

242
00:24:50.658 --> 00:24:52.871
Brother kills a brother...

243
00:24:52.951 --> 00:24:57.016
who's killed his father
who's killed his son.

244
00:24:57.096 --> 00:24:59.607
Fate. Drink, Caligula.

245
00:25:05.212 --> 00:25:07.107
After you, dear brother.

246
00:25:14.231 --> 00:25:15.547
Poor boy.

247
00:25:16.687 --> 00:25:18.158
When I am gone...

248
00:25:19.097 --> 00:25:21.043
Caligula will kill you.

249
00:25:22.314 --> 00:25:26.593
And then someone will kill Caligula.

250
00:25:32.776 --> 00:25:33.690
Unless...

251
00:25:34.230 --> 00:25:36.482
unless he is dead, before I am.

252
00:25:38.071 --> 00:25:40.565
You are looking not well at all!

253
00:25:56.178 --> 00:25:59.569
I, Caligula Caesar,

254
00:26:00.477 --> 00:26:04.148
command in the name
of the Senate and the people of Rome.

255
00:26:19.489 --> 00:26:23.952
<i>A brother kills a brother...
who kills his father...</i>

256
00:26:24.032 --> 00:26:25.857
<i>who kills his son...</i>

257
00:26:26.633 --> 00:26:28.135
<i>Fate...</i>

258
00:26:29.039 --> 00:26:31.398
<i>And then someone must kill Caligula...</i>

259
00:26:35.841 --> 00:26:37.174
He's going to kill me.

260
00:26:38.896 --> 00:26:41.353
You're safe, you're with me.

261
00:26:43.702 --> 00:26:45.177
He's going to kill us.

262
00:26:45.931 --> 00:26:48.828
Just the way he killed
our father, our mother...

263
00:26:49.630 --> 00:26:50.894
and our brothers.

264
00:26:55.940 --> 00:26:59.346
I am not going to die.

265
00:26:59.426 --> 00:27:00.946
You won't.

266
00:27:01.026 --> 00:27:03.986
You're his heir.
There is no one else.

267
00:27:05.159 --> 00:27:06.548
Yes, there is.

268
00:27:07.619 --> 00:27:09.190
There's Gemellus...

269
00:27:10.685 --> 00:27:12.032
and Claudius.

270
00:27:13.550 --> 00:27:17.421
Gemellus is too young,
Claudius is an idiot

271
00:27:17.501 --> 00:27:21.985
and Tiberius is old.
You will be Emperor. Soon.

272
00:27:28.844 --> 00:27:30.999
And you will be my queen.

273
00:27:31.581 --> 00:27:33.653
You can't marry your sister.

274
00:27:35.149 --> 00:27:38.245
- You can in Egypt.
- But we're in Rome

275
00:27:38.325 --> 00:27:40.379
and you're already promised.

276
00:27:45.135 --> 00:27:47.940
I know, to Ennia...

277
00:27:58.926 --> 00:28:00.732
It's only a bird.

278
00:28:09.223 --> 00:28:09.940
Prince?

279
00:28:11.013 --> 00:28:11.827
What is it?

280
00:28:12.708 --> 00:28:13.232
My wife.

281
00:28:17.226 --> 00:28:18.648
Ennia!

282
00:28:35.019 --> 00:28:38.618
Now you are a man, Caligula.
What are you going to do?

283
00:28:39.477 --> 00:28:42.982
You must be the master
of your own destiny.

284
00:28:43.435 --> 00:28:47.148
Take it... with both hands.

285
00:29:12.240 --> 00:29:13.985
Cretins!

286
00:29:14.065 --> 00:29:16.482
Why did you permit him to do it?

287
00:29:19.335 --> 00:29:20.565
Bind his wrists.

288
00:29:21.958 --> 00:29:23.711
Bind his wrists!

289
00:29:30.658 --> 00:29:32.690
You must not go,
you must not leave me.

290
00:29:32.810 --> 00:29:34.523
You're my friend, my only friend.

291
00:29:35.477 --> 00:29:39.440
I've lived too long, Tiberius,
I hate my life.

292
00:29:40.490 --> 00:29:41.561
Leave us!

293
00:29:42.312 --> 00:29:43.190
Both of you!

294
00:29:43.916 --> 00:29:46.377
The man to choose
the hour of his own death

295
00:29:46.457 --> 00:29:49.940
is the closest he will ever
come to tricking fate.

296
00:29:50.741 --> 00:29:53.375
And fate decrees that when you die,

297
00:29:53.455 --> 00:29:55.104
Macro will kill me.

298
00:29:55.184 --> 00:29:57.482
I'll arrest him
and have him executed.

299
00:29:57.971 --> 00:30:00.414
You can't, he controls you.

300
00:30:01.021 --> 00:30:03.815
Anyway, even with Macro dead,

301
00:30:04.447 --> 00:30:09.065
how could I go on living
with this reptile?

302
00:30:12.556 --> 00:30:15.523
You will respect my friend always,
won't you, reptile?

303
00:30:15.643 --> 00:30:18.273
I've always respected him, lord.

304
00:30:18.643 --> 00:30:22.891
- You hear?
- Tiberius, you were wise once.

305
00:30:22.971 --> 00:30:25.523
Don't taunt me. I am old.

306
00:30:26.184 --> 00:30:28.482
I watched you grow into a monster.

307
00:30:29.435 --> 00:30:32.648
One by one, I've seen
you murder your family,

308
00:30:32.768 --> 00:30:35.755
your friends,
the noblest men in Rome.

309
00:30:35.835 --> 00:30:38.890
- That is treason.
- No, it's the truth.

310
00:30:40.594 --> 00:30:43.523
I am and always have been
surrounded by enemies.

311
00:30:44.668 --> 00:30:46.232
In my own family...

312
00:30:46.969 --> 00:30:48.503
in the Senate...

313
00:30:49.810 --> 00:30:50.900
You're cruel!

314
00:30:50.980 --> 00:30:55.898
No, honest. Old men
can sometimes see the future.

315
00:30:56.647 --> 00:31:03.198
So, from evils past
and evils yet to come,

316
00:31:04.669 --> 00:31:07.644
I now choose to escape.

317
00:31:17.723 --> 00:31:20.026
So these are your precautions, Nerva?

318
00:31:53.780 --> 00:31:58.480
- Nerva, what's it like?
- Warm, no pain...

319
00:31:59.094 --> 00:32:01.027
just drifting away.

320
00:32:01.557 --> 00:32:03.670
- Do you see her?
- Who?

321
00:32:03.750 --> 00:32:05.148
The goddess, Isis.

322
00:32:05.747 --> 00:32:07.739
So you're one of those who believe...

323
00:32:07.819 --> 00:32:09.541
Do you see her?

324
00:32:11.300 --> 00:32:13.672
- No.
- Are you sure?

325
00:32:19.051 --> 00:32:23.218
You're almost dead. What's it like?
What's happening to you now?

326
00:32:24.289 --> 00:32:25.280
Nothing.

327
00:32:26.037 --> 00:32:27.422
You're lying.

328
00:32:27.502 --> 00:32:30.607
You can see her.
I know you can. What is she like?

329
00:32:30.687 --> 00:32:31.677
No...

330
00:32:33.358 --> 00:32:35.082
nothing at all...

331
00:32:37.084 --> 00:32:38.107
just...

332
00:32:39.773 --> 00:32:41.073
sleep...

333
00:32:42.477 --> 00:32:43.648
Liar!

334
00:34:04.073 --> 00:34:07.699
Since Nerva died, Tiberius
has been half paralyzed.

335
00:34:07.779 --> 00:34:11.932
- They say he's close to death.
- Tiberius dies, be worse for us.

336
00:34:12.012 --> 00:34:14.857
- You love the bastard.
- Take that back!

337
00:35:04.729 --> 00:35:05.606
Prince...

338
00:35:06.219 --> 00:35:08.103
the physician Charicles.

339
00:35:27.048 --> 00:35:28.476
How is the Emperor?

340
00:35:29.252 --> 00:35:30.857
How long will he last?

341
00:35:30.977 --> 00:35:33.732
Well, it could happen any moment,
but with care

342
00:35:33.852 --> 00:35:35.565
he might last a year or so.

343
00:35:41.435 --> 00:35:43.023
I can smell death...

344
00:35:44.490 --> 00:35:45.716
but whose?

345
00:35:45.796 --> 00:35:46.893
Don't worry.

346
00:35:47.446 --> 00:35:49.331
He can do nothing without me.

347
00:35:50.288 --> 00:35:53.597
So these poor unfortunate
creatures thought...

348
00:35:54.979 --> 00:35:56.854
and where are they?

349
00:35:56.934 --> 00:35:58.023
No, Macro.

350
00:35:59.081 --> 00:36:00.523
He's planning something.

351
00:36:01.047 --> 00:36:02.593
You'll be Emperor, soon.

352
00:36:16.166 --> 00:36:17.380
You swear.

353
00:36:17.988 --> 00:36:18.845
I sw...

354
00:36:37.679 --> 00:36:39.100
I swear.

355
00:37:23.840 --> 00:37:24.315
Leave.

356
00:37:25.618 --> 00:37:26.815
Everyone leave.

357
00:38:14.175 --> 00:38:15.523
Tiberius.

358
00:38:22.667 --> 00:38:24.065
Tiberius.

359
00:39:32.229 --> 00:39:34.032
Caligula?

360
00:39:35.741 --> 00:39:36.190
Lord.

361
00:39:38.134 --> 00:39:40.523
Give me my ring.

362
00:39:49.190 --> 00:39:49.815
No.

363
00:39:51.318 --> 00:39:52.232
Yes.

364
00:40:04.453 --> 00:40:05.950
You...

365
00:40:06.030 --> 00:40:07.647
do not...

366
00:40:07.727 --> 00:40:08.565
dare!

367
00:40:09.518 --> 00:40:10.539
Prince.

368
00:40:10.619 --> 00:40:13.565
You do not dare!

369
00:41:27.170 --> 00:41:28.482
Hail, Caesar.

370
00:41:31.715 --> 00:41:33.089
Hail, Caesar.

371
00:41:33.169 --> 00:41:35.179
I'll get everyone assembled in the hall.

372
00:41:36.061 --> 00:41:37.451
For the announcement.

373
00:42:27.912 --> 00:42:28.690
Gemellus?

374
00:42:32.558 --> 00:42:33.773
Gemellus!

375
00:42:41.148 --> 00:42:42.632
Hail, Caesar.

376
00:42:46.620 --> 00:42:47.721
Gemellus...

377
00:42:49.130 --> 00:42:50.440
we are alone.

378
00:42:58.530 --> 00:43:00.440
We must love each other.

379
00:43:14.172 --> 00:43:18.414
Rest, Tiberius Caesar.

380
00:43:21.593 --> 00:43:26.538
Hail, Caligula Caesar.

381
00:43:31.950 --> 00:43:33.482
It's just like the dream.

382
00:43:37.011 --> 00:43:40.624
It's only his mask.
You are Caesar now.

383
00:43:42.109 --> 00:43:43.371
Caesar.

384
00:43:43.451 --> 00:43:48.195
Caesar, Emperor of Rome,
lord of the world.

385
00:43:49.259 --> 00:43:51.337
Lord of the world...

386
00:43:52.864 --> 00:43:54.898
I like this dream.

387
00:44:16.186 --> 00:44:17.050
At the...

388
00:44:25.816 --> 00:44:30.893
At the insistence of the Senate
and the people of Rome...

389
00:44:32.057 --> 00:44:33.232
I accept...

390
00:44:34.437 --> 00:44:35.376
humbly...

391
00:44:36.944 --> 00:44:40.107
the highest office
of our great republic.

392
00:44:46.547 --> 00:44:47.857
Our great republic!

393
00:45:07.158 --> 00:45:09.480
Where's the onion?
Give me the onion.

394
00:45:36.645 --> 00:45:38.232
When our beloved Tiberius was dying...

395
00:45:38.688 --> 00:45:41.232
- To the Tiber with Tiberius!
- Yes!

396
00:45:43.102 --> 00:45:44.898
- Throw him in the river!
- Yes!

397
00:45:47.532 --> 00:45:50.872
Tiberius! Throw him!
Throw him to the dark!

398
00:45:50.952 --> 00:45:54.357
Today we begin a new era.

399
00:45:55.014 --> 00:45:57.982
I grant a general amnesty.

400
00:45:58.102 --> 00:45:59.815
Hail!

401
00:46:00.768 --> 00:46:02.857
Caesar! Caesar!

402
00:46:08.408 --> 00:46:09.492
Silence!

403
00:46:11.489 --> 00:46:12.815
Silence!

404
00:46:12.935 --> 00:46:15.315
Great Caesar is not finished.

405
00:46:22.462 --> 00:46:23.903
As my fellow consul,

406
00:46:23.983 --> 00:46:26.832
the Senate and the people of Rome...

407
00:46:26.912 --> 00:46:29.940
have wisely chosen
my learned uncle Claudius.

408
00:46:30.213 --> 00:46:31.773
Hail, Claudius!

409
00:46:32.893 --> 00:46:34.773
Take your place
beside me, Claudius.

410
00:46:39.806 --> 00:46:41.879
Caesar Caligula...

411
00:46:41.959 --> 00:46:42.893
Take your place...

412
00:46:42.973 --> 00:46:44.663
I mean consul...

413
00:46:52.549 --> 00:46:55.336
I herewith adopt
as my son and heir...

414
00:46:55.881 --> 00:46:57.107
the prince Gemellus.

415
00:46:58.004 --> 00:46:59.940
- Come forward, prince.
- Hail, Gemellus!

416
00:47:14.439 --> 00:47:15.717
From this moment,

417
00:47:15.797 --> 00:47:19.278
all official oaths will contain
the following phrase:

418
00:47:20.293 --> 00:47:24.777
"I will value neither my life,
nor the lives of my children,

419
00:47:25.296 --> 00:47:27.997
any more highly
than I do the Emperor..."

420
00:47:28.077 --> 00:47:31.257
Hail! Hail! Hail!

421
00:47:32.025 --> 00:47:34.565
"...and of his sister, Drusilla."

422
00:47:43.852 --> 00:47:47.023
- Hail, Drusilla!
- Hail, Caligula!

423
00:47:56.450 --> 00:47:57.940
We must be careful of him.

424
00:48:02.926 --> 00:48:04.357
Oh, Claudius?

425
00:48:05.310 --> 00:48:07.607
No, Gemellus.

426
00:48:09.997 --> 00:48:12.920
Oh, yes... Gemellus.

427
00:48:18.823 --> 00:48:22.665
Did you see their faces when I told them
they had to swear not only to me,

428
00:48:23.166 --> 00:48:24.215
but to you?

429
00:48:24.900 --> 00:48:26.507
They were appalled.

430
00:48:28.661 --> 00:48:30.023
I do hope so.

431
00:48:30.446 --> 00:48:31.690
But is it wise?

432
00:48:39.717 --> 00:48:40.975
I can do...

433
00:48:50.859 --> 00:48:52.675
anything I like...

434
00:48:57.476 --> 00:48:58.769
to anyone.

435
00:49:00.734 --> 00:49:02.586
Well, don't start with me.

436
00:49:05.413 --> 00:49:06.834
Who would you suggest?

437
00:50:08.185 --> 00:50:10.523
Get out! Out!

438
00:50:13.676 --> 00:50:14.690
Who?

439
00:50:15.787 --> 00:50:17.482
Why not start with Macro?

440
00:50:18.497 --> 00:50:20.815
- Macro?
- Yes.

441
00:50:20.935 --> 00:50:24.148
Before he controls you
as he controlled Tiberius.

442
00:50:27.304 --> 00:50:30.398
Superb display, Macro, superb.

443
00:50:37.677 --> 00:50:39.065
Fetch me Gemellus.

444
00:50:39.811 --> 00:50:41.057
What? Here?

445
00:50:43.276 --> 00:50:45.390
Yes, here. Now.

446
00:50:52.394 --> 00:50:54.317
- Charicles.
- My lord?

447
00:50:54.397 --> 00:50:55.369
Stand here.

448
00:51:01.017 --> 00:51:03.184
I want a bonus for my guards.

449
00:51:03.264 --> 00:51:04.856
But, Caesar,
that's not possible.

450
00:51:04.936 --> 00:51:06.984
All things that happen
are possible, Longinus.

451
00:51:07.064 --> 00:51:09.357
Make the impossible happen
and it would be possible. Logical?

452
00:51:09.477 --> 00:51:12.067
How, Caesar?
The deficit, you see, is...

453
00:51:12.147 --> 00:51:14.063
Look, how much is my purse?

454
00:51:14.645 --> 00:51:17.380
Well, lord, that is as much
as you may require.

455
00:51:17.460 --> 00:51:18.940
Oh, good.

456
00:51:19.507 --> 00:51:23.107
Macro, would you stand over there?

457
00:51:27.854 --> 00:51:29.857
Longinus, you here.

458
00:51:30.221 --> 00:51:31.360
Yes, Caesar.

459
00:51:32.953 --> 00:51:38.970
Gemellus, I want you to look
at these gentlemen very carefully.

460
00:51:40.185 --> 00:51:43.823
Take your time and tell me...

461
00:51:44.462 --> 00:51:47.898
who killed our beloved Tiberius?

462
00:51:54.596 --> 00:51:56.648
Who killed Tiberius?

463
00:52:13.981 --> 00:52:14.732
He did!

464
00:52:16.717 --> 00:52:17.482
Macro!

465
00:52:27.333 --> 00:52:28.642
Murderer.

466
00:52:38.587 --> 00:52:40.065
Arrest him.

467
00:52:56.862 --> 00:53:00.357
In honor of your
new commander, Chaerea...

468
00:53:01.735 --> 00:53:03.982
ten gold pieces to every man.

469
00:53:04.102 --> 00:53:07.107
Hail! Hail! Hail!

470
00:53:10.192 --> 00:53:12.565
Chaerea, arrest Macro.

471
00:53:12.685 --> 00:53:14.637
Guards, arrest Macro.

472
00:53:17.435 --> 00:53:18.759
Don't you dare!

473
00:53:49.121 --> 00:53:50.273
Forgive me, Caesar...

474
00:53:52.670 --> 00:53:53.647
Chaerea.

475
00:53:53.727 --> 00:53:55.934
Two senators beg to see you.

476
00:53:56.014 --> 00:53:57.607
They have a dispute over land

477
00:53:57.727 --> 00:53:59.523
and await your judgment.

478
00:54:00.233 --> 00:54:01.565
Well, bring them in.

479
00:54:01.645 --> 00:54:02.676
Bring them in.

480
00:54:03.739 --> 00:54:06.767
I'm interested in all that is Rome,

481
00:54:06.847 --> 00:54:09.607
even down to the length of the toga.

482
00:54:10.052 --> 00:54:10.966
Come now.

483
00:54:25.518 --> 00:54:27.482
Caesar, I must complain
about the bov...

484
00:54:27.602 --> 00:54:29.315
Give me the documents.

485
00:54:57.405 --> 00:54:59.857
- Guilty.
- Thank you, thank you.

486
00:55:00.276 --> 00:55:01.273
Don't thank me.

487
00:55:02.620 --> 00:55:06.220
Justice must always be impartial.

488
00:55:06.300 --> 00:55:07.107
That is so, Chaerea.

489
00:55:08.675 --> 00:55:09.857
Is it not?

490
00:55:10.321 --> 00:55:11.232
Yes, Caesar.

491
00:55:12.551 --> 00:55:13.583
You may go.

492
00:55:51.923 --> 00:55:52.893
Ennia.

493
00:56:02.525 --> 00:56:03.685
You look beautiful.

494
00:56:11.758 --> 00:56:13.482
Is it good for growing hair?

495
00:56:15.426 --> 00:56:19.016
We'll be married soon.
The divorce will only take a few days.

496
00:56:22.259 --> 00:56:24.315
- I think we should move.
- Move?

497
00:56:24.822 --> 00:56:25.768
Where?

498
00:56:27.514 --> 00:56:29.123
Alexandria, say.

499
00:56:30.779 --> 00:56:32.187
To Egypt?

500
00:56:33.420 --> 00:56:34.315
Yeah.

501
00:56:36.053 --> 00:56:37.482
What do you think?

502
00:56:37.602 --> 00:56:41.846
I'd hate to leave Rome.
I mean, the Senate...

503
00:56:41.926 --> 00:56:43.732
No, no, Ennia, I am Rome.

504
00:56:44.565 --> 00:56:46.757
Wherever I am, Rome is.

505
00:56:46.837 --> 00:56:49.940
And there is the Senate
and the people of Rome.

506
00:56:52.804 --> 00:56:55.725
You do make me laugh
the way you say that.

507
00:57:05.977 --> 00:57:09.746
- Ah, Longinus.
- Forgive us, Caesar.

508
00:57:14.783 --> 00:57:16.315
Longinus, is it done?

509
00:57:16.768 --> 00:57:18.898
The Senate has
sentenced him to death.

510
00:57:22.999 --> 00:57:24.045
The commission.

511
00:57:29.506 --> 00:57:32.157
Chaerea, I now officially appoint you

512
00:57:32.237 --> 00:57:34.065
commander of my imperial guard.

513
00:57:36.228 --> 00:57:40.166
But what about Macro?
What's happened? Where is he?

514
00:57:40.246 --> 00:57:41.815
He has been arrested for treason.

515
00:57:43.245 --> 00:57:44.315
That's impossible.

516
00:57:45.013 --> 00:57:47.188
Caesar, you know
he worshipped you.

517
00:57:47.268 --> 00:57:48.802
He made you.

518
00:57:56.178 --> 00:58:00.815
- Nobody made me.
- I... I can't believe it.

519
00:58:01.613 --> 00:58:03.315
What did he do?

520
00:58:04.486 --> 00:58:05.553
Ennia...

521
00:58:06.648 --> 00:58:10.217
I had to take my destiny
with my own hands.

522
00:58:22.007 --> 00:58:22.773
Guards.

523
00:58:27.724 --> 00:58:30.009
Chaerea, she's to be banished.

524
00:58:30.985 --> 00:58:33.040
- I love you.
- To Gaul.

525
00:58:33.610 --> 00:58:34.212
Lift!

526
00:58:34.292 --> 00:58:35.491
I love you.

527
00:58:37.610 --> 00:58:41.235
Caligula, how could you do it?
He was your friend.

528
00:58:41.315 --> 00:58:43.855
He would've done
anything for you.

529
00:58:43.935 --> 00:58:45.190
Don't send me away!

530
00:58:46.370 --> 00:58:47.760
I love you!

531
00:58:48.636 --> 00:58:50.176
Caligula!

532
00:58:53.612 --> 00:58:56.357
Now at least she doesn't
have to get a divorce.

533
00:58:56.477 --> 00:58:58.982
But you still have to find
a suitable wife.

534
00:59:00.049 --> 00:59:00.744
No.

535
00:59:06.639 --> 00:59:08.410
I'm going to marry you.

536
00:59:09.061 --> 00:59:11.634
You can't, we're not Egyptians.

537
00:59:12.960 --> 00:59:13.440
I know.

538
00:59:15.102 --> 00:59:17.374
We are much more beautiful.

539
00:59:17.454 --> 00:59:19.148
Rome is not Egypt.

540
00:59:19.820 --> 00:59:22.468
And stop looking
at yourself like that.

541
00:59:25.438 --> 00:59:28.729
- Let's go to Egypt then.
